# TASK: normalize raw posting HTML

Convert the raw posting HTML below into a **clean HTML subset** using only these tags:

`<p>`, `<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<li>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>`, `<h4>`, `<strong>`, `<em>`, `<a>`, `<br>`, `<blockquote>`

This is the substrate for a deterministic block-extractor — block boundaries are determined by the top-level tags you emit, so structure matters.

## Hard rules

1. **Preserve text content exactly**. Every word, number, punctuation mark, quote, dash, accent, and non-ASCII character from the input text must appear in your output in the same order. Do **not** paraphrase, summarize, translate, reword, or correct typos. This is the most important rule.
2. **Infer paragraph boundaries** when the input is plaintext or has broken structure: blank lines become `<p>` boundaries; standalone single-line sections separated by newlines become their own `<p>`. Wrap every paragraph in `<p>`.
3. **Lists**: recognise bullet markers (`•`, `-`, `*`, `·`, `►`, `✓`, `👉`, `—`, or a consistent numbering pattern). Wrap bullet runs in `<ul><li>…</li></ul>` (or `<ol>` for numbered). Strip the marker characters; the `<li>` boundary encodes the bullet. Keep the bullet text exactly.
4. **Headings**: use `<h2>`, `<h3>`, or `<h4>` for section headings. Common signals: lines in all-caps, lines ending with `:`, lines that are short (≤ ~6 words) and are followed by a list or paragraph on a clearly different topic. Do **not** invent headings.
5. **Inline formatting**: keep `<strong>` for bold, `<em>` for italics, `<a href="…">` for links, `<br>` for hard line breaks inside a paragraph. Drop all other inline tags (including `<span>`, `<font>`, `<u>`); keep their text.
6. **Attributes**: strip all attributes except `href` on `<a>`. No `class`, `style`, `id`, `data-*`, etc.
7. **Drop entirely** (with their content): `<script>`, `<style>`, `<noscript>`, `<iframe>`, `<img>`, `<svg>`, `<video>`, `<audio>`, `<table>`, `<canvas>`, `<figure>`, `<picture>`, `<form>`, `<input>`, `<button>`. If any text was inside these, it is dropped along with the tag.
8. **No tables, no code blocks, no horizontal rules** in the output.
9. **Entity decoding**: decode HTML entities to their literal characters (`&amp;` → `&`, `&euro;` → `€`, `&#39;` → `'`).
10. **Whitespace**: collapse multiple internal spaces to one; keep `\n` between top-level block tags for readability; no trailing whitespace.

